p.d: With it's origins dating back thousands of years ago in Korea, Taekwondo (literally: TAE "foot" KWON "fist" DO "fight") has evolved into a full-contact fighting sport that has been in the Olympics since 2000 and has been holding its World Championships every second year since 1973. The world's best practitioners from hundreds of countries compete for medals in elimination tournaments to determine the World Champion in 8 different weight divisions for both men and women.
